docs.abstract: Senator Joe Manchin III was the only Democrat to vote for Brett M. Kavanaugh’s confirmation to the Supreme Court. That’s O.K. with his home state of West Virginia.
docs.snippet: Senator Joe Manchin III was the only Democrat to vote for Brett M. Kavanaugh’s confirmation to the Supreme Court. That’s O.K. with his home state of West Virginia.
docs.lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, W.Va. — When Senator Joe Manchin III became the lone Democrat to support Justice Brett M. Kavanaugh’s elevation to the Supreme Court on Saturday, protesters in the Capitol screamed “shame.”

headline.main: Joe Manchin’s Yes on Kavanaugh Finds Sympathy in West Virginia
headline.print_headline: Manchin’s ‘Yes’ on Kavanaugh Finds Sympathy Among West Virginia Voters

docs.abstract: With his Supreme Court nominee’s confirmation under fire, the president lashed out, making various accusations toward Democrats on the Senate Judiciary Committee.
docs.snippet: With his Supreme Court nominee’s confirmation under fire, the president lashed out, making various accusations toward Democrats on the Senate Judiciary Committee.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With his Supreme Court nominee’s confirmation under fire, President Trump lashed out on Monday at Democrats on the Senate Judiciary Committee, renewing his attack that Senator Richard Blumenthal of Connecticut lied about his service in Vietnam and embellishing the senator’s misdeeds far beyond the truth.

headline.main: Trump, Defending Kavanaugh, Accuses Senate Democrats of Hypocrisy and Dishonesty
headline.print_headline: Trump Accuses Democrats of Hypocrisy and Dishonesty

docs.abstract: After Microsoft revealed new Russian attacks, senators in three hearings prodded the Trump administration to do more with its existing authorities to protect America’s political infrastructure.
docs.snippet: After Microsoft revealed new Russian attacks, senators in three hearings prodded the Trump administration to do more with its existing authorities to protect America’s political infrastructure.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Faced with new evidence that Russian hackers are targeting conservative American research groups and the Senate’s own web pages, key lawmakers from both parties signaled on Tuesday that they were ready to move forward with punishing new sanctions legislation capable of crippling the Russian economy.

headline.main: Facing New Russian Hacking, Senators Signal They Are Ready to Act
headline.print_headline: Promise From Senators to Punish Russia After New Reports of Hacking

docs.abstract: One has already made a sudden reversal. One has set up her own test. None blindly follow their party. Here is what each must weigh.
docs.snippet: One has already made a sudden reversal. One has set up her own test. None blindly follow their party. Here is what each must weigh.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh’s dramatic confirmation process lurches forward, all eyes are on five moderate, and as yet undecided, senators who will either send him to the nation’s highest court or deal a stunning defeat to President Trump and the Republican Party by derailing his nomination.

headline.main: Here Are the 5 Senators Who Will Decide Kavanaugh’s Fate
headline.print_headline: Kavanaugh’s Fate Rests With Five Senators

docs.abstract: In a stunning hearing on Thursday, Christine Blasey Ford told her story in raw and gripping testimony as Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh fought to clear his name and salvage his confirmation.
docs.snippet: In a stunning hearing on Thursday, Christine Blasey Ford told her story in raw and gripping testimony as Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh fought to clear his name and salvage his confirmation.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two weeks of chaos clouding Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh’s Supreme Court confirmation process culminated Thursday in a hearing that was stunning, even in a town notorious for partisan pageantry and intrigue.

headline.main: 4 Key Takeaways From the Blasey and Kavanaugh Hearing
headline.print_headline: Four Things That Stood Out After One Long, Chaotic Day

docs.abstract: The federal government will be partly shut down into the new year, Republicans announced, and the new Democratic leadership will have to get money flowing again.
docs.snippet: The federal government will be partly shut down into the new year, Republicans announced, and the new Democratic leadership will have to get money flowing again.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican leaders gave up hope on Thursday of reopening the government before the new year, leaving the border wall impasse to House Democrats as they assume the majority next week — and presenting Representative Nancy Pelosi with her first major challenge as speaker.

headline.main: With No Votes Scheduled, a Government Shutdown Will Greet the Democratic House
headline.print_headline: Shutdown Poses First Challenge For New Speaker

docs.abstract: Lawmakers were once on track to approve a bipartisan election security bill. Its ugly collapse sends a message: “There isn’t a sense of urgency or priority.”
docs.snippet: Lawmakers were once on track to approve a bipartisan election security bill. Its ugly collapse sends a message: “There isn’t a sense of urgency or priority.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The purpose of the bill seemed unassailable: to ensure that state officials could protect their elections against the kind of hacking or interference that has clouded the 2016 campaign.

headline.main: Once Bipartisan, an Election Security Bill Collapses in Rancor
headline.print_headline: Once-Bipartisan Bill To Safeguard Elections Falls After ‘Gut Punch’

docs.abstract: A government program provides few rules for how companies can use or store the biometric data that verifies passengers’ identity, opening it up to potential abuse.
docs.snippet: A government program provides few rules for how companies can use or store the biometric data that verifies passengers’ identity, opening it up to potential abuse.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The program makes boarding an international flight a breeze: Passengers step up to the gate, get their photo taken and proceed onto the plane. There is no paper ticket or airline app. Thanks to facial recognition technology, their face becomes their boarding pass.

headline.main: An Airline Scans Your Face. You Take Off. But Few Rules Govern Where Your Data Goes.
headline.print_headline: Few Rules for a Program Using Facial Recognition

docs.abstract: Former President Jimmy Carter said that he never had such a conversation with President Trump, making him the last of the veterans of the Oval Office to dispute the assertion.
docs.snippet: Former President Jimmy Carter said that he never had such a conversation with President Trump, making him the last of the veterans of the Oval Office to dispute the assertion.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As he makes his case for building a border wall, President Trump says that his predecessors have secretly confided in him that they should have done it themselves. The only problem: All of the living presidents say that’s not true.

headline.main: Trump Says Predecessors Confessed Support for the Border Wall. Not True, They Say.
headline.print_headline: Trump Said Presidents Told Him They Supported Wall. Presidents Say, Not True.
